fights.userDescription: Sayali could barely touch Mahima as the latter surged with confidence. Sayali's frustration at not beating Mahima in IFC was visible as she tried her best in vain. Eventually, Mahima finished her with a cool nasty kick to the face that knocked her out.

Brutal bloody fight. Hetal started dominantly as she ripped apart Unnati's dfenses and broke her side rib. Unnati managed to brave through that injury and mount a stunning comeback. It wasn't easy as both fighters showed their ruthlessness and why they are called champions. Ultimately, Unnati let out a blitzkrieg and ripped apart Hetal to win.
Komal is fighting like a champion as she defeated Aishwarya perfectly. She's slowly got the tactical mind of being in a title hunt.

Sayali was in perfect zen mode as she navigated the dangerous kicks and strikes from Rushika. It was a replica of the peace and calmness that had helped her land the Season 7 title. However, one powerful stray kick from Rushika betrayed Sayali. The power behind that kick was enough to confuse a poor Sayali who was then beaten to crap by a rampant Rushika. Rushika saved the best for last as she withdrew just before Sayali would be knocked out only to place a steely kick that knocked out the former champion to the relegation zone.

Kinjal showed all the finer nuances of a professionally trained MMA fighter competing at the highest level as she dispatched off Kripa Jalan with barely any impactful strikes hitting herself. Kinjal was exceptional as she struck with inch-perfect accuracy before taking Kripa down with a perfect triangle choke and blasting away her face with incredibly strong punches. A majestic win!
A quick in and out affair as Unnati barely gave Aishwarya chance to strike and wrapped her in a cold rear naked choke hold to finish the fight. Confidence.

10 seconds knockout. Sayali took 10 seconds to weight her opponent before feigning a thunderous tornado trick kick to shock Komal. Komal never got a chance to use her skills or strike as she was cleanly knocked out by the power of that kick. Sayali followed it up with brutal punches to all but wrap up the win.

Mahima was left speechless as Rushika finished her with lethal Taekwondo kicks. Rushika was excellent at finding gaps and applying just the right pressure to derail Mahima. The impact of the kicks was so strong that Mahima was already dizzying by the second kick. The rest were just additions to knock Mahima out. A kicky stunning affair with a toned body for Rushika.

Kinjal was doing just great as she inflicted some serious strikes on Venessa without a reply. That was until Venessa attempted her first few strikes and a nasty hook to the side completely derailed Kinjal. Kinjal was unable to get past the pain and Venessa used her distraction to full use as she brought her down and pounded her to a win.
Sayali had no chance as Unnati wrecked havoc with Hetal present in the stands.

Komal was clearly the better fighter and outclassing Mahima until the final third of the fight. Mahima was left annoyed and frustrated by how Komal was able to fight better than her. So, Mahima opted for a random vicious street-style brawling that surprised both the referee and Komal. Komal still managed to have the upper hand until the last five minutes where Mahima called back her supreme skillsets to place Komal in a rear-naked choke to end the fight.

Venessa was dominant in the first half where she nearly decimated Rushika without giving her a space to breathe. When Rushika finally composed herself, she took little time to take back the dominance and then using her strong kicks, destroyed Venessa. Both used their respective skills to the fullest.
Unnati ripped apart Mahima ferociously. Mahima's leg was the first to be shattered before the former unleashed hell.

Surreal power in the kick as Rushika blanks out Komal with a powerful kick to the face after Komal manages to trap her kick. Rushika was constantly peppering Komal with nasty powerful kicks before that thunderbolt. She finished off the fight with some good old punches to the face.
Three powerful kicks were the highlight of the fight that completely derailed Venessa.
Brutal but perfect kicks by Kripa.
Vicious by Sayali, back in form.
Furious win. Hetal doesn't wait for a post-fight conference as she storms out of the arena and sits in her car after losing the top spot and Invicta Cup in Australia.

Ishita was dominant at the start, but Krishi remained resilient. Eventually, Krishi managed to overpower Ishita. She finally trapped her against the cage and choked her. When Ishita was fairly subdued, Krishi took her to the ground and gave Ishita a good old ground and pound to win.
Supriya was listless as Hinal ran circles around her and finally deservingly won the fight.
Amruta was phenomenal as she matched Isha's energy and wrapped up the fight with a majestic triangle choke while resisting Isha's move to lift her up while in triangle choke. Ferocious!

Bullish win for Anmol Pandya who gave no chance and no space to Vinaya for any strike. Anmol used her heavy body to her full advantage as she kept taking down Vinaya before raining blows on her. Every kick and punch was devastating as she bullied Vinaya to win this fight. Championesque win for Anmol!
Bullish win. Zero strikes by Anika.

It started with Ishita dominating the fight. Amruta slowly and steadily grew into the fight before taking control over the fight and eventually taking dominance over the IFC #3. By the end of the fight, Ishita was hapless as a brilliant Amruta Date recorded one of the biggest win in her MMA career.
Commendable fighting spirit by Hinal, but Anmol was simply too good for her.

Amruta was supremely dominant and wasted no time in this 1.5 mins fight. She parried a teep kick from her elder sister and retorted back with a powerful right hook to the jaw. It was followed by a knee kick to the solar plexus before taking Ashwini down and locking her in a superb guillotine choke that the latter couldn't escape out of. A difference of miles between the two sisters as Amruta looks all set to rub shoulders with the elite.
Dominant champions like performance from Isha Nagar who gave no chance to Hinal for striking back

Anmol is unstoppable. She was perfect and destructive as she took apart Krishi after some initial difficulty. Krishi, on her part, looked the champion as she matched Anmol's physicality, presence, and strength. However, eventually, she steadily lost control of the fight , Anmol showed her efficiency and dominance as she tore apart Krishi with ease and broke her arm before finishing off the challenge with a perfect powerful kick to the face.

Clear difference in the hunger to win as a rampant Amruta ripped apart Vinaya to go three points clear at the top. Amruta was far too skilled as Vinaya could barely contain Amruta. The former ended the fight avec un acrobatic finish.
Ishita vent out all her fury on Ashwini.
Drishti has been working extremely hard on her legs as her insanely muscular legs were responsible for the victory. She followed it up with some brutal elbow strikes that all but sealed the win.

Ananya was brutal as she dispatched off Jinali. The fighters started equal with equal strikes and blows. However, somewhere in the middle, Ananya took control and then, it was one-side traffic. Displaying her smart intelligence, Ananya showed her research as she picked up on all the weak spots of Jinali leaving aside the latter's strength.

Bandgee was dominant 95% of the fight with Kanchan barely managing to scrap some significant strikes. She had to execute her chokehold three times before she managed to get it right and take out Bandgee. Bandgee has truly reached the potential of a Division 1 or Division 2 fighter.
Aashna convincingly trapped Drishti in a leg lock and an arm bar to break her arm and nose. Finished it with a spectacular kick to the face.
Sayali who is set to fight Ananya in Invicta Cup could only watch in awe as the 19-year old dispatched off Tanvi brutally.

Vidhi was brilliant and destructive. She could have brutally damaged Shraddha. However, Shraddha chose the right time to drop in a rear naked choke and that ended all the challenge. Vidhi still struggled to get free but Shraddha managed it well.

Mridula totally nullifies Bandgee. Bandgee was barely there in the fight as Mridula dominated for at least 98% of the fight. Bandgee took Mridula's 12 strikes to hit her first. In totality, Bandgee had only 6-7 significant strikes while Mridula crossed 50. Mridula also broke Bandgee's right leg and brutalised her way to a massive confident victory.

Dominant and bullish win for Drishti. Ananya was sorely missing as her first strike which was the first strike in the fight had no impact on Drishti. After that, it was majorly Drishti and her legs who bullied Ananya and eventually won via ground and pound.

Tanvi was brutal and confident from the start. Isha could barely reply to Tanvi's agility and kicks. However, one spectacular block to a roundhouse kick and Isha slowly started gaining momentum. Eventually, Isha combined a leg lock to a rear naked choke and that was more than Tanvi could handle.
Tanvi was far too dominant against Shraddha and should have won the fight. Shraddha was lucky she persisted till the end and managed to wrap Tanvi in a good rear naked choke to win.

Diana was excellent and should have been the winner. It was an agonisingly long fight as equals. Both fighters were persistent although it looked like Diana needed this more than Kanchan. Eventually, Kanchan managed to trap Diana in a rear naked chokehold.

Aashna was majestic. Kanchan never bad a chance to strike Aashna. Aashna was supremely professional and insanely calm as she thwarted every Kanchan strike and struck back stronger. Eventually that perfect chokehold was enough to bring a historic win. A win that reminds of her glory days when she chased the title.
Kanchan rips apart Ananya's face in a vicious war that saw them engage in an intense street style battle for win.

Vicious battle as the two fighters looked to be on a personal agenda to finish each other off. Fight moved from a professional environment to a poor impression of a street brawl. There was viciousness in every strike but poorly executed at times. All in all, pure entertainment as both were equal until the end when Ananya's kick surprised Bandgee. Ananya finished it off with a flurry of punches.

Supreme skills by Vidhi to dodge Sachi's incoming strike, move behind her, shove her to the right distance before unleashing a lethal kick to the jaw that knocked Sachi out. To ensure the win, Vidhi dropped nasty punches and elbows and even a rear naked chokre but by then, the victory was already done and acquired.

Shraddha started strong and it gave a lot of hope to Mridula sitting in the stands to finish second. Shraddha's strikes were strong and they were finding gaps accurately. However, Kanchan flipped the tables suddenly and put on such a dominating force that Shraddha couldn't handle. Eventually, Kanchan let out her anger and brutally disfigured Shraddha to confirm her second place finish this season while breaking her arm.

Kriti reserved one of her best performances for the last as she dominated and beat Aashna down to mincemeat. This was a flawless top-notch performance of highest professional standards that got Krishi to the top ten in IFC rankings earlier in the season. They was just about perfect power behind each strike, perfect accuracy, and lethal skills at display with merciless brutality as she won against an in-form Aashna Jogani.

The most brutal fight was reserved for the last fight of Division 3. Diana absolutely battered the shit out of Mridula in the first half. Mridula had no answer whatsoever as she Diana rained punches, kicks and holds. However, Diana was this close to finishing off the fight when Mridula made an epic comeback. Having stronger legs than her Australian counterpart and more agility, Mridula ripped apart the challenge to pieces and brutally destroyed Diana by breaking her arm and her face to win the fight.
